Reasoning: The paper deals with coding for interactive communication in the presence of noisy channels that can perform insertions and deletions of symbols. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.CC). The paper also discusses the concept of edit distance tree codes, which is a novel primitive, and this could potentially fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
